      "description": "Presenting an impeccable 997.1 Carrera S, featuring the robust 3.8L M97.01 flat-six powerplant delivering 355 hp with a linear torque curve. This example boasts a pristine DME overrev report and has undergone a comprehensive borescope inspection to confirm cylinder wall integrity. The 6-speed manual transaxle is paired with a factory short-shift kit, offering precise gate engagement and mechanical tactile feedback. Performance is bolstered by Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. Every bushing, seal, and fluid is current, ensuring the telepathic steering rack and high-revving throttle response remain true to Weissach\u2019s original specifications. A concours-level specimen for the discerning collector.",
